response.Q0: I started by examining the nodes that led to more choices, and then examining the choices branching from those nodes; I changed my strategy halfway through to starting from the furthest nodes and picking a high-scoring one. I also learned that clicking on the first-level nodes actually earned me a bit of money so I started doing that.
response.Q1: I changed it to inspecting final-level nodes after I realised that the value ranges for the nodes grew with distance from the centre.
response.Q2: It took me about halfway through the game, so it was quite difficult; the lack of information and the fact that I had started off not exploring the full range of node levels were the problem.
